  "title": "Vet Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>🐾 Now Hiring: Lead Veterinary Technician / DVM</strong><br>\n<em>Location:</em> Holland Village / Ang Mo Kio<br>\n<em>Employment Type:</em> Full-Time</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>About Us</strong><br>\nOmniVet is a progressive veterinary practice dedicated to delivering exceptional pet care and fostering a supportive team environment. We’re looking for an experienced</p>\n<p><strong>Lead Veterinary Technician / DVM</strong> to guide our nursing team, manage clinic operations, and oversee inventory control.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Position Overview</strong><br>\nThis leadership role blends hands-on clinical work with team management and operational oversight. The Lead Veterinary Technician / DVM will work alongside veterinarians, lead and mentor vet nurses, and ensure the clinic runs smoothly through efficient inventory management and process improvements.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Lead, supervise, and mentor veterinary nurses to maintain high standards of patient care</li>\n  <li>Perform veterinary examinations, diagnostics, and treatments as needed</li>\n  <li>Assist in surgical procedures and oversee post-operative care</li>\n  <li>Manage medical inventory — order supplies, track stock levels, and ensure timely replenishment</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with safety, hygiene, and medical protocols</li>\n  <li>Conduct staff training, performance reviews, and workflow planning</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with management to improve clinical and operational efficiency</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Doctor of Veterinary Medicine (DVM)</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Minimum 2 years’ experience in a veterinary clinical setting</strong></li>\n  <li>Strong leadership, communication, and interpersonal skills</li>\n  <li>Excellent organizational and problem-solving abilities</li>\n  <li>Ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with veterinary inventory systems is an advantage</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What We Offer</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Competitive salary and benefits package</li>\n  <li>Opportunities for leadership and professional growth</li>\n  <li>A collaborative, pet-loving workplace culture</li>\n  <li>Staff discounts on veterinary services and products</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>How to Apply</strong><br>\nPlease email your CV and a cover letter to OmniVet.hr@gmail.com with the subject line <strong>\"Application – Lead Veterinary Technician / DVM\"</strong>.<br>\n</p>\n<p>Lead with compassion, inspire your team, and help us deliver the best care for pets and their families. 🐶🐱</p>",
